<!-- ============= Introduction ============================== -->
<sect1 id="geyes-introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>
<!-- ==== Figure ============================================= -->
	 <figure id="geyes-fig"> 
		<title>&applet; Applet</title> 
		<screenshot> 
		  <mediaobject> 
			 <imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/geyes_applet.png" format="PNG"/> 
			 </imageobject>
			 <textobject> 
				<phrase>Screenshot of the Geyes applet.</phrase> 
			 </textobject> 
		  </mediaobject> 
		</screenshot> 
	 </figure> 
    <!-- ==== End of Figure ======================================= -->
<para>The <application>&applet;</application> applet enables you to track the movement of 
the mouse pointer around the desktop. The applet is an image of one or more
eyes that follow the mouse pointer around the screen.</para>
<para>To add <application>&applet;</application> to a panel, right-click on the panel to open the panel menu, then choose  <menuchoice>
<guimenu>Add to panel</guimenu>
<guisubmenu>Amusements</guisubmenu>
<guimenuitem>Geyes Applet</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>.</para>
</sect1>
<!-- ============= Settings  ================================ -->
<sect1 id="geyes-settings">
<title>Settings</title>
<para>To configure <application>&applet;</application>, right-click on the <application>
&applet;</application> applet, then choose <guimenu>Properties</guimenu> from the applet popup menu. </para>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Theme Name</guilabel> </term>
<listitem>
<para>Choose a theme for <application>&applet;</application> from this list.
Themes range from Bizarre to Horrid to provide a different look for <application>
&applet;</application>.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</sect1>
